            <title><![CDATA[PopArabia acquires Viral Wave, marking A15’s ninth exit]]></title>
                        <description><![CDATA[<ul>
	<li>Egypt-based VC firm A15 has marked its ninth exit with the acquisition of its portfolio company Viral Wave by PopArabia.</li>
	<li>Founded in 2023 as part of ARPUPlus, Viral Wave is a UAE-based digital music distribution platform, managing content across streaming platforms and YouTube.</li>
	<li>Post-acquisition, Viral Wave will operate as PopArabia&rsquo;s distribution and label services division, with its Egypt-based team integrated into regional operations.</li>
	<li>The deal expands PopArabia and Reservoir&rsquo;s footprint across MENA, strengthening capabilities in music distribution, monetisation, and artist services.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Press release:</strong></p>

<p>A15, a Cairo-based early-stage venture capital firm focused on the MENA region, today&nbsp; announced the acquisition of Viral Wave, an A15 portfolio company, by PopArabia, a partner in the&nbsp; MENA region to NASDAQ-listed Reservoir (NASDAQ: RSVR). The transaction represents A15&#39;s ninth exit&nbsp; and further demonstrates the firm&#39;s consistent track record of backing outliers and delivering returns to&nbsp; its investors.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Spun out from ARPUPlus, A15&#39;s venture-building arm, Viral Wave is a UAE-headquartered music digital&nbsp; distribution company providing end-to-end services across digital distribution, YouTube management,&nbsp; and monetisation on major global streaming platforms. The company has administered a catalog&nbsp; generating over 55 billion streams, with a roster of established and emerging regional artists including&nbsp; Ramy Sabry, Ramy Gamal, Ahmed Saad, Tamer Ashour, Ruby, Saber Rebai, Didine, and Shehab.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>Under the terms of the acquisition, Viral Wave will serve as PopArabia&#39;s dedicated distribution and label&nbsp; services division. Viral Wave&rsquo;s Egypt-based team will be integrated into PopArabia&#39;s regional operations,&nbsp; combining complementary capabilities across distribution, digital monetisation, and artist services&nbsp; across MENA. The transaction also further extends the international footprint of PopArabia&rsquo;s partner,&nbsp; New York-based Reservoir.&nbsp;</p>

<p>A15&#39;s nine exits span fintech, media and advertising, enterprise services, and consumer applications,&nbsp; reflecting the firm&#39;s sector breadth and its disciplined approach to value creation across the full&nbsp; investment lifecycle.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Karim Beshara, A15 Managing Partner, commented: &quot;A15&#39;s ninth exit is a meaningful milestone,&nbsp; and one that reflects the consistency our team has built over more than two decades of investing&nbsp; and company-building.&#39; We are proud of what the Viral Wave and ARPUPlus teams have&nbsp; achieved, and we congratulate them on reaching this outcome. We wish the Viral Wave team&nbsp; every success as they embark on this next chapter under Reservoir and PopArabia&#39;s global&nbsp; platform.&quot;&nbsp;</p>

<p>Medhat Karam, ARPUPlus CEO, added &quot;We are proud to have supported Viral Wave from&nbsp; inception through to this strategic outcome. Building enduring companies requires patience,&nbsp; operational depth, and a long-term commitment to the teams and markets we back. We&nbsp; congratulate the Viral Wave team and wish them continued momentum as they integrate into&nbsp; one of the region&#39;s most significant music platforms.&quot;&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
